Class TradingStrategy

java.lang.Object
TradingStrategy
All Implemented Interfaces:
TradingStrategyInterface
public class TradingStrategy extends Object implements TradingStrategyInterface
This class represents a trading strategy. It includes the name of the strategy, the coin in interest, the current price of the coin, the target price of the coin, and the action it will take.
Author:
Nicholas Lai, Samuel Catania

  • Constructor Details

    • TradingStrategy

      public TradingStrategy(String strategyName, String coinTarget, String action, int quantity, boolean quantityIsCount, String[] names, String[] symbols, int[] prices)
      Constructor for TradingStrategy creates a new TradingStrategy
      Parameters:
      strategyName - name of strategy
      coinTarget - coin that will be traded
      action - buy/sell
      quantity - amount of coin will be bought/sold OR the total price of the amount of coin to be bought/sold
      quantityIsCount - true if quantity is the amount of coin, false if it is the price.
      names - String array of the names of the coins.
      symbols - String array of coin tickers (eg. BTC for bitcoin)
      prices - int array of current coin prices

    • trade

      public String[] trade(String brokerName, double coinTargetPrice, String[] coinList, double[] coinPriceList)
      Method trade executes a trade.
      Specified by:
      trade in interface TradingStrategyInterface
      Parameters:
      brokerName - name of broker
      coinTargetPrice - target price of coin
      coinList - list of coins attached to the broker
      coinPriceList - list of coin prices associated with the coins attached to the broker.
      Returns:
      a String[] that contains details about the trade that was performed.
